			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>Hello,</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I am lvl 11 and so far things seem good. I enjoy playing&nbsp; pet class but I am having problems with controlling the pet.&nbsp; I pull a mob&nbsp;and the mob comes and maybe one or two more. I bring the mob(s) to camp only to find the pet banging on one of the adds. I spam hit the "Back" key because if i hit it once, he take a few steps toward me then continues attacking when I dont want him to. I hit "Sit" key and he sits for about a second then starts attacking again after hittin the "Back" key.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It is impossible to get him to attack the mob I want to kill first with other mobs attacking me. Basically I have to kill all the other mobs&nbsp;first until the mob I want him to attack is the only one left. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So he is deciding what mobs I kill first. True i could just let him kill one and I take another but sometimes I want both of us on the same mob especially tougher encounters. So my question is, does controlling pets get better as I get higher lvl pets (Besides the Pet hold AA)?. &nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Also, My lvl 8 pet cant hold arrgo for crap. I send him in and wait till the mob is at like 70%.. I walk up to it and it immediately turns to me. I havent done a thing to it.. just got close.. even though it says it is taunting.. I dont think it is.. or if it is , it&nbsp;is basically worthless.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Do we get pet buffs that allow it to add hate to its taunt? AA&nbsp;maybe? CA? &nbsp;or, is the taunt broke and a known issue? I have read through the boards but cant seem to find something specific to what i am posting about. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Any info would be greatly appreciated..</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Thanks</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>EDIT: Forgot one more thing, can BST pets use weapons like Mage pets? If so, what weapons can I get for my pet that wont Poof every time i dismiss him or he is killed? </DIV></DIV><p>Message Edited by Talsmar on <span class=date_text>09-11-2006</span> <span class=time_text>04:40 AM</span>	
		</td></tr>
