<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=beastlord&message.id=5220#M5220">2</a> of 26
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1432 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;
<HR>
Talsmar wrote:<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>Hello,</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I am lvl 11 and so far things seem good. I enjoy playing&nbsp; pet class but I am having problems with controlling the pet.&nbsp; I pull a mob&nbsp;and the mob comes and maybe one or two more. I bring the mob(s) to camp only to find the pet banging on one of the adds. I spam hit the "Back" key because if i hit it once, he take a few steps toward me then continues attacking when I dont want him to. I hit "Sit" key and he sits for about a second then starts attacking again after hittin the "Back" key.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It is impossible to get him to attack the mob I want to kill first with other mobs attacking me. Basically I have to kill all the other mobs&nbsp;first until the mob I want him to attack is the only one left. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So he is deciding what mobs I kill first. True i could just let him kill one and I take another but sometimes I want both of us on the same mob especially tougher encounters. So my question is, does controlling pets get better as I get higher lvl pets (Besides the Pet hold AA)?. &nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></DIV>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>In this situation this is a normal occurance. How it works is your pet will normally attack the first mob that did damage to your character,be it melle,DD,AE or DoT.&nbsp; With that being said often in cases where you agro more then one mob the pet will sometimes bounce between the two . As an example say this happens. You run up and agro a mob and inadvertanly get an add that was in line of sight range of the mob you agroed and was assisted. On your way back to camp the mob you originally pulled manadged to get in a hit or a nuke while the second one never touched you. Pet goes for the one that hit you as normal and the second starts hitting on you. Now the pet which went for the 1st one starts hitting on it therefore gaining its attention while your left on the second one. If your a considerable distance between your pet the pet back off command will rarely work seeing as the mob that attacked your pet damadged it so therefore your pet will stick on that mob no matter how many times you hit the back off command. In early levels before AA's the best way to try to compensate for this is staying close to your pet and hope it ping pongs on the one you want it to attack. Meaning if a mob is hurting your character&nbsp;to the point where the pet consideres it a threat it will turn to attack the mob thats hitting your character&nbsp;while still mantaining the 1st mobs attention till they both mobs&nbsp;are dead. To answer your second question it doesnt really get any different based on level but more on AA's (pet hold, pet focus) those AA's better allow us to keep better controll of our warders.</DIV>
<DIV><BR>
<HR>
Talsmar wrote:<BR></DIV>
<DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Also, My lvl 8 pet cant hold arrgo for crap. I send him in and wait till the mob is at like 70%.. I walk up to it and it immediately turns to me. I havent done a thing to it.. just got close.. even though it says it is taunting.. I dont think it is.. or if it is , it&nbsp;is basically worthless.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Do we get pet buffs that allow it to add hate to its taunt? AA&nbsp;maybe? CA? &nbsp;or, is the taunt broke and a known issue? I have read through the boards but cant seem to find something specific to what i am posting about. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></DIV>
<P>Message Edited by Talsmar on <SPAN class=date_text>09-11-2006</SPAN> <SPAN class=time_text>04:40 AM</SPAN><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>This is also another common occurance shared between all pet classes. As a general rule a PC thats on the mobs hate list will always take agro from a pet by just walking in its attack area reguardless on what the mobs health is at since the pet itself is considered an NPC. While there is no way to change this you can compensate this be it solo or when you do group CC or for pet tanking just by backing away from the mob and pet. The mob will immideatly return its attention to the pet.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P><BR>&nbsp;</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Talsmar wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>EDIT: Forgot one more thing, can BST pets use weapons like Mage pets? If so, what weapons can I get for my pet that wont Poof every time i dismiss him or he is killed? </DIV></DIV>
<P>
<HR>

<P>Beast pets can use weapons like mage pets can, it just wont display an equipped graphic. Unfortunatly to answer the second part of the question anything you give to your pet will poff when he is dismissed or killed. Later on when you get the AA's suspend minion and persistent minion that will allow you to keep a pet on hold and let it retain what buffs and or items that you gave to it untill either it dies or your character dies.
<P>&nbsp;
<P>Hope all this helps to answer your questions<img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><BR>&nbsp;</P></BLOCKQUOTE><BR><BR></DIV></DIV>	
