<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=beastlord&message.id=5222#M5222">4</a> of 26
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1412 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Talsmar wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>Do we get pet buffs that allow it to add hate to its taunt? AA&nbsp;maybe? CA? &nbsp;or, is the taunt broke and a known issue? I have read through the boards but cant seem to find something specific to what i am posting about. <BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>The buffs you get for your pet actually add to it's taunt in addition to doing the DD.&nbsp; If you find yourself needing a minute to recover health or something eventually you'll reach the point where you can't just back off your pet because the mob will follow you.&nbsp; Wait for the message that says your pet has damaged the mob with non-melee damage and you should be able to back up and bind wounds or cast heals or whatever it is you needed to do.<BR><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Talsmar wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>Wow thanks a bunch for the awesome reply.. Very informative.. Really appreciate the time spent in replying..</P>
<P>Just one more question, are there pet weapons I can buy in the Bazaar or are they all summoned by mages? If I remember correctly, </P>
<P>The way You determined a weapon is for pets is the class/race will say&nbsp; "None" is that correct?<BR>
<HR>
</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>A pet can use pretty much any weapon.&nbsp; However they follow the same rules as PC's do, generally speaking.&nbsp; For example, velium weapons won't proc their damage until your pet's 20th level.</P>
<P>There are other pet "toys" such as shields and muzzles etc that they can use and the descriptive text will explicitly state that they are to be used by pets.</P>
<P>I personally just ask /ooc if there are any Mages willing to summon pet toys for me in exchange for cash, euphemistically put as "donations".&nbsp; I haven't been here for the last few expansions, so I don't know if there are "better" pet toys available that I just haven't heard of yet.&nbsp; Some mages will just summon them for you for free, happy that someone finds them useful.&nbsp; <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></P>
<P>Given that a pet will run to intercept and attack a mob every time they see you damaged, there are ways to "get around" that until you get your hold AA.&nbsp; What I did, especially in outdoor zones, was put my pet a ways back from where I wanted to do my fighting.&nbsp; That way, my warder and I could meet in the middle, the middle being where I wanted to have the fight.</P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Bannor <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=954067">Dark Elf Beastlord</a>|<a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/lite/index.vm?characterId=601295490329&resize=no">EQ Lite Profile</a>
							</div>
								
