			There was a period of time where weapon type had an impact on our warders.&nbsp; That time has passed though.&nbsp; Right now you can give a warder a dagger, a sword, etc. and it won't have an impact.&nbsp; All that will matter is damage, proc, and "type"(meaning 1h, 2h).&nbsp; <br><br>Early on you can raise a warders damage a noticeable bit by giving them a hard hitting weapon, but later on that becomes very unlikely.&nbsp; At that point all that really matters is the proc.&nbsp; The warder can take advantage of dd procs, dot procs, or even utility procs(snare for instance is a popular one).<br><br><br><div></div>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>09-11-2006</span> <span class=time_text>04:00 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_rating_cell" valign=bottom nowrap 
			
			>
			
				&nbsp;
				
