		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			One trick to help to control the pet better before you get the AA's is to set up a pet attack social. Go to the socials page in the actions box (ctrl+o) click on the little arrow to go to a page with blank socials, right click a blank social. In the name box name it something like Pet Attk, on the first line enter " /pet back off "&nbsp; on the second line enter " /pet attack " . (without the quotation marks) Click accept, left click and hold the new social button to "lift" it and drop it in your hotkey box. The /pet back off command clears the pets personal hate list, making it more likely to attack and stick on the mob you have targeted. This isn't a cure all and you may have to spam it quite a few times to get your pet focused where you want, but it tends to work better than the simple pet attack button with more than one mob engaged. While you are in the socials page make a social called Assist with " /assist " in the first line and accept. This way you can target your pet by taping F1 twice, hit the assist hotkey and be targeted on the same mob your pet has targeted quickly. Good luck and good hunting. <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><br><div></div>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Tuga<br>Mistress of the Forge<br>Currently residing on Stromm
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
