			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=beastlord&message.id=5234#M5234">14</a> of 26
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1319 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Not totally sure on what you are asking, so here come some random answers lol.&nbsp; If I miss what you were asking, please try again.&nbsp; 8P<br><br>-&nbsp; The "type" of weapon, 1hs, 1hb, etc. has no impact on the performance of your warder.&nbsp; There was a time where this was the case, but that no longer matters.<br><br>-&nbsp; The weapon damage helps as long as the damage of the weapon reprsents a boost over what the warder would naturally hit for.&nbsp; For example, if a warder were naturally hitting for 20 and you gave them a weapon that made them hit for 24 then this would be a noteable boost in warder dps.&nbsp; It used to be amazing to give your warder a 2h weapon early in levels because the pet would hit for a *LOT* more damage and tear through monsters as their delay wasn't alterted by the weapons delay, but their damage went way up.&nbsp; <br><br>As levels increase the warder naturally hits for more and more and because of that it takes better and better weapons to actually make the warder hit for more damage.&nbsp; If you could someone get a weapon that made your warder hit for 100+ when it naturally hit for 80, then this would be a nice boost to damage, but finding such a one hander that you would give to the warder doesn't happen often.&nbsp; 8P<br><br>Thus, at lower levels you can give warders a nice 2h or even some 1h's and it works out well.&nbsp; However, at higher levels the damage of the weapon is less and less likely to matter, so then the proc becomes the main reason a weapon is given to the warder.&nbsp; *shrugs*<br><br>Hope that covers it, but I might have missed the mark some hehe.&nbsp; 8P<br><div></div>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
