		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P>I don't want to put too fine a point on it, but Beastlords don't have PETS, we have Warders. I know, they act like pets, and make messes in their litter boxes like pets, but they are not. </P>
<P>The distinction is that "pets" are temporary summoned pets, that poof when you are done with them. </P>
<P>Warders are the Beastlords spiritual companion, your partner for life. You do not summon a NEW warder, you RE-summon the old one again each time you play. It is a fine line I know. Think of Guenweyver from the Drizzit novels. </P>
<P>By the way, if you wanna argue the point,&nbsp; call Buffy a PET, she&nbsp;would be happy to rip off your arms and legs to convince you otherwise...........</P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
