		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			"pet" is the term I try to use when talking about "pets" in EQ.&nbsp; Meaning, necro pets, sk pets, beastlord warders, etc.&nbsp; Their isn't a /warder back off function I don't think, there isn't a "warder weapon" answer or a "warder filtering" to my knowledge.&nbsp; <br><br>Most of the time on the beastlord boards I'll use the term warder.&nbsp; ie.&nbsp; iksar beastlord warder bug, and warders with EF disc running.&nbsp; However, the overall game mechanic that "warders" belong to, is "pets" to my knowledge, so that is what I use when speaking generally.&nbsp; In the case of how weapons work on "pets" the same holds true for warders now as did for all "pets" back then.&nbsp; However, there was a time that the warder rules and "pet" rules were different.&nbsp; I try to use "pet" whenever talking about beastlord "warders" whenever the knowledge/data would also carry over to the other classes, so that I don't have a mage ask me "ok, so that's how warders work, but what about pets".&nbsp; <br><br>Very similiar thing used to happen to me when talking about enchatner "animations" verse "pets" back in the day.&nbsp; *shrugs*<br><br>You can put however fine a point on it you want, but be careful you don't put so fine a point on it that you leave out information.<br><div></div>	
		</td></tr>
