		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Right click on your chat window bar, should get a drop down menu of things to filter to that window. By default everything goes to your Main chat window. <br><br>I run with 3 windows myself. One for chat, one for melee/spell spam and the last is for critical stuff I don't want to miss. That one changes all the time depending on what I'm doing.<br><br>One more thing missed for pet mechanics. When your pet (warder for the pickier people) is placed on gaurd, it returns to the spot at a walk instead of a run. When the pet is in follow mode it will run back to you.<br><br>Why is this important? You put your pet on gaurd to go pull some mob and it nukes you on the way back. Your pet runs to the rescue and agros the mob. You tell your pet to /back off and it sulkily walks back to the spot it was told to stay at. Of course now the pet has the mobs attention and it keeps swinging, everytime the mob swings it reagros your pet.<br><br>Only two things you can do at this point. Run out and join your pet or tell your pet to follow. If you tell it to follow then /back off the pet will now happily run back to your side. Back off may still need to be spammed a few times because the mob keeps swinging but this becomes less of a problem when sow becomes available.	
		</td></tr>
